<doc id="550974" wikidata="Q7113586" url="?curid=550974" title="Overcast! (album)">
<text>Overcast! is the debut studio album by Minneapolis hip hop group Atmosphere, released on August 5, 1997, on Rhymesayers Entertainment. It is the only Atmosphere album to feature MC Spawn trading verses with Slug. Before the album&#x27;s release, Spawn left the group due to conflicting motives.

== Development ==
The cover art is inspired by that of &quot;Judgment!&quot;, released in 1964 by jazz pianist Andrew Hill. The album contains several tracks featured on &quot;Overcast!&quot; (EP), however notably absent is &quot;God&#x27;s Bathroom Floor&quot;.

== Releases ==
The album was remastered and re-released in 2017 with new artwork and bonus tracks.

==Track listing==
*All songs produced by Ant.
===2017 remaster bonus tracks===
